{"article_id":"bvRg8uFnNUDODog6","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"CINCINNATI -The impending nomination of a new U.S. Supreme Court justice means abortion opponents could be closer","depth":10},{"id":1,"text":"than they ' ve been in 45 years","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"to seeing the court overturn its landmark Roe v. Wade decision .","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"President Donald Trump ,","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"who is poised to select the next justice ,","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"has vowed","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"his choices for the court would \" automatically \" repeal the ruling .","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"But ending Roe won ' t end abortion in America - or the fight over abortion .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Instead , a repeal of Roe would shift the battle from the federal courts to state legislatures ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"where lawmakers in every state would make their own rules","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"about when , where and under what circumstances women could obtain abortions .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"States would be free to act","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"because ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"without Roe ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"the constitutional right","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"to access abortion","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"would be gone .","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"July 8 :","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"Trump legal adviser talks up Kavanaugh and Barrett for Supreme Court","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"July 8 :","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"President Trump taunts his political skeptics","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"while preparing second nominee to Supreme Court","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"\" All of a sudden , that ' s where the venue is , \"","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"said James Bopp Jr. , general counsel for National Right to Life .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"\" All federal oversight goes away . \"","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"Those on both sides of the debate say","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"the result would be a patchwork of new laws ,","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"with some states enacting outright bans ,","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"others setting tougher restrictions","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"and still others maintaining the status quo .","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"In this new landscape , some women could have access to abortions with few or no restrictions ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"while others would have to travel hundreds of miles or more","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"to find a clinic in another state .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"To some extent , this is already happening .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Republican state lawmakers across the country have been attacking Roe around the edges for years with increasingly restrictive rules , from gestational limits to tougher licensing for clinics .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Court challenges","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"based on Roe v. Wade","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"rolled back some of those rules , but not all of them .","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"The new restrictions contributed to the closing of more than 50 clinics nationwide between 2011 and 2014 ,","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"according to the Guttmacher Institute ,","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"which tracks abortion-related data .","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"Ohio , Michigan and Texas eachlost at least one-third of their clinics in that time .","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"A handful of states ,","depth":15},{"id":43,"text":"including Kentucky , Mississippi and Missouri ,","depth":15},{"id":44,"text":"are down to one clinic .","depth":14},{"id":45,"text":"Overturning Roe would accelerate the process ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"abortion rights activists say ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"because states would no longer have to worry about a federal judge","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"standing in their way .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"\" The right","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"to access abortion in this country","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"is on the line , \"","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"said Dawn Laguens , executive vice president of the Planned Parenthood Federation of America .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"A recent court case in Ohio offers a hint of how a post-Roe world would work .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"After the state legislature passed a law","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"banning abortion in cases","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"where a fetus is diagnosed with Down syndrome ,","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"U.S. District Judge Timothy Black blocked enforcement of the law .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Opinion :","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"Overturn Roe v. Wade :","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"Abortion debate , like death penalty , belongs in hands of citizens","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"July 6 :","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"For President Trump , Supreme Court nomination may hinge on Brett Kavanaugh 's risks and rewards","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"His ruling was based entirely on constitutional protections","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"granted by Roe v. Wade .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"\" A state may not prohibit any woman from making the ultimate decision","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"to terminate her pregnancy before viability , \"","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Black wrote .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"If Roe is overturned ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"that legal argument would vanish","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"and states like Ohio could make their own rules .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"\" Basically , the question would go to the states , \"","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"said Freda Levenson , legal director for the American Civil Liberties Union in Ohio .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"There ' s no way","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"to know for certain","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"how many states would ban abortion","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"or institute tougher restrictions","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"if given the chance ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"but at least a dozen , mostly in the South and Midwest , have given every indication","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"they ' re ready to act .","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Four states , Louisiana , Mississippi , North Dakota and South Dakota , have approved `` trigger laws ''","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"that would ban abortion","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"immediately after the Supreme Court overturns Roe v. Wade .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"Roughly a dozen other states appear unlikely to enact tougher abortion laws ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"and some of those , such as California and Maryland , have laws","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"explicitly protecting the right","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"to access abortion .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"Bopp said","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"states should be allowed to chart their own course ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"and overturning Roe is the only way .","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Roe took democracy out of the abortion equation","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"by declaring it a privacy right","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"protected by the U.S. Constitution .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"Without Roe ,","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"the people of every state could decide how tolerant or not they want to be","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"when it comes to abortion .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"\" We ' ve had little opportunity for the democratic process","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to sort this through","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"and develop a consensus , \"","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"Bopp said .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"\" It ' ll take some time . \"","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"July 6 :","depth":4},{"id":104,"text":"Abortion-rights activists send hangers to Sen. Collins ,","depth":5},{"id":105,"text":"hoping to influence her vote on court","depth":5},{"id":106,"text":"Opinion :","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"Their goal of Roe v. Wade reversal in sight ,","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"many Republicans have private second thoughts","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"In theory , such a process could force state legislatures to compromise .","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"For 45 years , lawmakers on both sides could be as strident","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"as they liked","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"because they knew","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"the courts , ultimately , would sort it out","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"and that Roe would prevent an outright ban .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"If Roe goes away ,","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"laws","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"that previously would have been rejected by the courts","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"will have real consequences , not only for pregnant women ,","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"but for politicians , too .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"Navigating the new terrain won ' t be easy .","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"A Pew Research Center poll last year found","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"most Americans are somewhere in the middle on abortion .","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"Overall , 57 percent said","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"it should be legal in all or most cases","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"and 40 percent said","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"it should be illegal in all or most cases .","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"But those with absolutist views are in the minority :","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"Just 25 percent said","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"abortion should be legal in all cases","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"and 16 percent said","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"it should be illegal in all cases .","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"Views vary from state to state , however ,","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"and abortion rights activists say","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"that ' s why leaving the decision to lawmakers is a problem .","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"They say","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"an individual ' s rights shouldn ' t be subject to the beliefs of the majority of voters in the place","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"they happen to live .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"\" Some states probably wouldn ' t impose restrictions","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"and some would impose terrible restrictions , \"","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"Levenson said .","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"\" Some states are poised to go","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"as far","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"as they can . \"","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"July 5 :","depth":3},{"id":145,"text":"President Trump narrows Supreme Court search ,","depth":4},{"id":146,"text":"focuses on three judges","depth":4},{"id":147,"text":"July 5 :","depth":3},{"id":148,"text":"These five senators could make or break Trump 's Supreme Court nominee","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":297,"left":292,"right":296,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":292,"left":251,"right":291,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":251,"left":209,"right":250,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":209,"left":206,"right":208,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":165,"right":205,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":156,"right":164,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":155,"right":7,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":155,"left":151,"right":154,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":150,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":153,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":153,"left":152,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":158,"right":163,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":8,"right":157,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157